                            <comment id="15338024" author="smilegator" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2016 16:54:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let me work on it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15338096" author="smilegator" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2016 18:22:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;: ) Found a more serious bug in Json when reading the related code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15338104" author="cloud_fan" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2016 18:40:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yea go ahead, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15338128" author="smilegator" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2016 19:41:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks! In Spark 2.0, the simplest solution is to put &lt;tt&gt;comment&lt;/tt&gt; into &lt;tt&gt;metadata&lt;/tt&gt; of &lt;tt&gt;StructField&lt;/tt&gt;. However, in the long term, I think we need to consolidate &lt;tt&gt;StrcutField&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;CatalogColumn&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15338148" author="smilegator" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2016 20:09:11 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;  test(&quot;desc table for parquet data source table&quot;) {
    val tabName = &quot;tab1&quot;
    withTable(tabName) {
      sql(s&quot;CREATE TABLE $tabName(a int comment &apos;test&apos;) USING parquet &quot;)

      checkAnswer(
        sql(s&quot;DESC $tabName&quot;).select(&quot;comment&quot;),
        Row(&quot;test&quot;)
      )
    }
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried both catalogs (in-memory catalog and hive metastore). The above test case can pass in both cases. Could you explain a little bit more about the exact scenario?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
